   "body" : "Since the minimum signed integer cannot be represented as positive so long as its type is signed, and it's not well-defined what happens if you make it unsigned before negating it, we instead increment the negative integer by 1, convert it, then increment the (now positive) unsigned integer by 1 to compensate\n\n@wizeman recently introduced this potential-bug in #1298, so I'd appreciate if he could comment (did not get a response on IRC)",
